WEBVTT

00:01.468 --> 00:02.802
- [car horn honks]
- ♪ School is out ♪

00:02.869 --> 00:03.937
♪ The day is done ♪

00:04.003 --> 00:06.272
♪ But for you
it's just begun ♪

00:06.339 --> 00:07.574
♪ Welcome home ♪

00:07.640 --> 00:10.510
♪ Welcome to The Wayne ♪
- ♪ I'm so glad you came ♪

00:10.577 --> 00:12.679
- ♪ Around every corner ♪

00:12.746 --> 00:15.415
♪ Behind every door ♪

00:15.482 --> 00:17.784
♪ Adventure is waiting ♪

00:17.851 --> 00:20.920
♪ So no hesitating ♪

00:20.987 --> 00:23.189
- ♪ Explore ♪
- ♪ What you can't explain ♪

00:23.256 --> 00:25.859
{\an5}- ♪ Explore ♪
- ♪ Welcome to the Wayne ♪

00:25.925 --> 00:28.495
- ♪ Explore ♪
- ♪ Welcome to the Wayne ♪♪

00:32.232 --> 00:34.300
{\an8}- ♪

00:34.367 --> 00:36.069
{\an8}- [grunts]

00:37.137 --> 00:38.304
{\an8}- Are you galloping?

00:38.371 --> 00:39.773
{\an8}- I never graduated
to skipping.

00:39.839 --> 00:41.074
{\an8}They kept holding me back.

00:41.141 --> 00:43.109
{\an8}- Well, hi ho Silver
yourself this a-way.

00:43.176 --> 00:44.544
{\an8}We've got to get to the roof.

00:44.611 --> 00:46.846
{\an8}Saraline said she might know
what to do with these cards.

00:46.913 --> 00:48.415
{\an8}- So we found
three magical cards

00:48.481 --> 00:50.950
{\an8}with our names on them
in the Wayne secret library.

00:51.017 --> 00:52.352
I mean, it's exciting,

00:52.419 --> 00:54.854
but so is Becky Steingold's
shiny watch in math class.

00:54.921 --> 00:56.156
At least I think
it's math class.

00:56.222 --> 00:57.690
I have no idea
what we're studying.

01:00.260 --> 01:03.296
- Those kids appear
to have found some artifacts.

01:03.363 --> 01:06.366
- Let me guess.
Cards covered in symbols?

01:06.433 --> 01:07.634
- MASTERSON: How did you know?

01:07.700 --> 01:08.635
- Get them.

01:08.701 --> 01:12.005
- ♪

01:12.071 --> 01:13.740
- And also, pick up some milk.

01:13.807 --> 01:14.641
- Two percent?

01:14.707 --> 01:15.642
- Almond.

01:15.708 --> 01:17.377
- ♪

01:17.444 --> 01:18.812
- It's different for you, Olly.

01:18.878 --> 01:20.213
You've always lived here.

01:20.280 --> 01:22.715
I've spent my whole life
moving from place to place.

01:22.782 --> 01:24.150
I never really fit in anywhere.

01:24.217 --> 01:25.852
- You fit in this elevator
pretty well.

01:25.919 --> 01:27.420
- Getting these cards
makes me think

01:27.487 --> 01:29.189
maybe I was meant
to come to the Wayne.

01:29.255 --> 01:31.891
Why else would our names
be on them?

01:31.958 --> 01:33.326
- BOTH: Masterson!

01:33.393 --> 01:35.361
- Thanks a lot
for holding the doors for me.

01:35.428 --> 01:36.362
Jeez.

01:36.429 --> 01:37.730
- Sorry. We didn't see you.

01:37.797 --> 01:39.432
Also, you're kind of our enemy.

01:39.499 --> 01:42.101
- Yeah, I guess there's that.

01:42.168 --> 01:44.070
Anyway, give me those cards.

01:44.137 --> 01:46.806
- [grunting]

01:46.873 --> 01:47.740
- Ah, time out, time out.

01:47.807 --> 01:49.242
I've got something in my eye.

01:49.309 --> 01:51.144
- Just blink a few times.

01:51.211 --> 01:52.145
It'll come out.

01:52.212 --> 01:53.546
- I got it. Time in.

01:56.015 --> 01:58.017
- [grunting]

01:58.084 --> 01:59.619
- Best two out of three?

01:59.686 --> 02:00.954
- [elevator dings]

02:01.020 --> 02:02.555
- ♪

02:02.622 --> 02:04.724
- Is there
some sort of problem here?

02:04.791 --> 02:05.725
- Not at all.

02:05.792 --> 02:07.460
I was just leaving.

02:09.496 --> 02:10.830
A minor setback.

02:13.700 --> 02:14.701
- Jonah Bishop!

02:14.767 --> 02:15.735
- Olly.

02:15.802 --> 02:17.437
- How's about
a little hero worship?

02:17.504 --> 02:18.771
- No, thank you.

02:18.838 --> 02:20.306
- I meant me worshiping you,
in case that wasn't clear.

02:20.373 --> 02:21.908
- No.
- Uh, no, it wasn't clear?

02:21.975 --> 02:23.109
Or, no, you don't have time?

02:23.176 --> 02:25.211
- No to everything.

02:25.278 --> 02:26.312
- [elevator dings]
- Pardon me.

02:26.379 --> 02:28.014
Important package man
coming through

02:28.081 --> 02:30.250
with important packages here.

02:30.316 --> 02:33.319
- George, are you sure
you haven't seen my package?

02:33.386 --> 02:35.388
It's red, L-shaped,
and it's tied--

02:35.455 --> 02:36.589
- With yellow string. Yeah.

02:36.656 --> 02:38.558
Yeah, I heard you
the first few times.

02:38.625 --> 02:41.060
Oh, I also appreciated
that you--

02:41.127 --> 02:42.462
- [gasps]
- --painted it for me.

02:42.529 --> 02:45.798
And this didn't at all insult
my intelligence, by the way.

02:45.865 --> 02:48.635
- Jonah, we can help you
find your missing package.

02:48.701 --> 02:50.370
- No.

02:50.436 --> 02:52.138
- Can you at least
look at these cards?

02:52.205 --> 02:53.540
- You kids
really don't understand

02:53.606 --> 02:56.242
the most basic social cues,
don't you?

02:56.309 --> 02:58.077
- I think he's saying
he likes us.

02:58.144 --> 02:59.846
- Please, I don't have time.

02:59.913 --> 03:03.383
Leave me alone.

03:03.449 --> 03:04.684
- You just can't get
a straight answer

03:04.751 --> 03:06.553
out of some people.

03:06.619 --> 03:07.954
- SARALINE: So far,
the only spectrum of light

03:08.021 --> 03:09.722
it responds to is ultraviolet.

03:09.789 --> 03:11.291
- [machine beeps]

03:11.357 --> 03:12.926
- What do you think, Pracky?

03:12.992 --> 03:15.895
- If I had feelings,
which I don't,

03:15.962 --> 03:17.830
I'd share them with you.

03:17.897 --> 03:19.132
- Oh, Pracky.
- Hey, Saraline.

03:19.198 --> 03:20.600
- [gasps]
- Aah! Pracky!

03:20.667 --> 03:23.336
I thought Mom and Dad made you
throw that out years ago.

03:23.403 --> 03:24.704
- Friendship is forever,
Olly...

03:24.771 --> 03:26.839
especially when
it's not biodegradable.

03:26.906 --> 03:28.007
- Oh, what's a Pracky?

03:28.074 --> 03:29.409
- Pracky the practice friend.

03:29.475 --> 03:31.678
Don't you remember
the commercials?

03:31.744 --> 03:32.845
- ♪ Pracky ♪

03:32.912 --> 03:34.380
♪ Oh, Pracky ♪

03:34.447 --> 03:35.815
♪ A practice friend ♪

03:35.882 --> 03:37.550
♪ With 21 phrases ♪

03:37.617 --> 03:38.785
♪ Pracky ♪

03:38.851 --> 03:39.886
♪ Talks backy ♪

03:39.953 --> 03:41.087
- Am I alive?
- ♪ He'll be ♪

03:41.154 --> 03:43.523
♪ One of your child's
craziest phases ♪♪

03:43.590 --> 03:44.757
- Okay, okay.

03:44.824 --> 03:47.226
So maybe making friends
was never my strong suit.

03:47.293 --> 03:49.095
- That's because you
think about it too much.

03:49.162 --> 03:50.763
Just go with the flow.

03:50.830 --> 03:52.198
That's my life philosophy.

03:52.265 --> 03:53.800
I saw it on a shirt.

03:53.866 --> 03:55.001
- That doesn't work.

03:55.068 --> 03:56.035
- Sure it does.

03:56.102 --> 03:57.103
Think about our adventures.

03:57.170 --> 03:58.571
Things always work out.

03:58.638 --> 03:59.839
It just happens.

03:59.906 --> 04:02.175
- It just happens because
I ask important questions.

04:02.241 --> 04:03.476
- And I come up with a plan.

04:03.543 --> 04:06.713
- Right! But to me,
it just happens.

04:06.779 --> 04:09.048
- I've run my card
through a series of tests.

04:09.115 --> 04:10.783
- So? Have you
figured out what it is?

04:10.850 --> 04:12.251
A message? A map?

04:12.318 --> 04:14.887
- A coupon to Splitsville--that
banana split place for couples

04:14.954 --> 04:16.221
in failing relationships?

04:16.289 --> 04:17.557
- Inconclusive.

04:17.624 --> 04:20.125
But the material it's made of
seems indestructible.

04:20.192 --> 04:21.226
Until we find out more,

04:21.293 --> 04:23.262
we can't let these cards
out of our sight.

04:23.329 --> 04:25.131
They could be dangerous.

04:25.198 --> 04:26.265
- So what's the plan?

04:26.332 --> 04:27.400
- Just let it happen?

04:27.467 --> 04:28.501
- SARALINE AND ANSI: No.

04:28.568 --> 04:30.603
- I have one idea,
but it's a longshot.

04:30.670 --> 04:33.139
When we were in the Stanza,
I found a book.

04:33.206 --> 04:34.540
- [machine beeps]

04:34.607 --> 04:37.844
- If this is the Wayne
and this is one of the cards,

04:37.910 --> 04:42.715
then holding them up to the sky
might activate something.

04:42.782 --> 04:45.618
- [beeping]

04:49.188 --> 04:50.223
- Is anything happening?

04:50.289 --> 04:51.290
- Not yet.

04:51.357 --> 04:53.126
Raise your right arm
a little higher.

04:53.192 --> 04:54.761
- Now lift one leg,
puff out your chest,

04:54.827 --> 04:58.097
and swivel your butt
in a circular motion.

04:58.164 --> 04:59.899
- You sure this is
what the book says?

04:59.966 --> 05:01.601
- What book?
- Olly!

05:01.668 --> 05:03.302
- [sighs]
- What's wrong, Sis?

05:03.369 --> 05:04.771
- Nothing. Just...

05:04.837 --> 05:07.373
I wish I had a best friend
to annoy like that.

05:07.440 --> 05:09.742
- Saraline,
making friends is easy.

05:09.809 --> 05:12.045
If you go with the flow,
I bet you could be best friends

05:12.111 --> 05:13.312
with the next person you see.

05:13.379 --> 05:14.814
- You think?

05:14.881 --> 05:16.516
- Huzzah, Team Timbers!

05:16.582 --> 05:19.952
'Tis I, Leif Bonnewell III.

05:20.019 --> 05:21.487
- No.

05:21.554 --> 05:23.656
- It looks like you're up to
one of your little adventures--

05:23.723 --> 05:25.792
not that any of you bothered
to call me about it.

05:25.858 --> 05:28.161
It's almost as though
you've forgotten that I'm--

05:28.227 --> 05:31.564
- ♪

05:31.631 --> 05:33.166
- [whispers] --The Asset.

05:33.232 --> 05:34.901
- Friendship
challenge accepted.

05:34.967 --> 05:36.169
- Not Leif.

05:36.235 --> 05:38.071
He's un-friendable,
and not just on social media.

05:38.137 --> 05:39.639
- Exactly.

05:39.706 --> 05:42.008
If I can make friends with Leif,
I can make friends with anyone.

05:44.343 --> 05:45.511
Hi, Leif.

05:45.578 --> 05:48.381
Always glad to have you
along for a mission.

05:48.448 --> 05:50.249
- Yes. Now make it your mission

05:50.316 --> 05:51.784
to fetch me
a bottle of club soda--

05:51.851 --> 05:53.019
shaken, not stirred.

05:53.086 --> 05:53.953
Andy boy!

05:54.020 --> 05:55.021
- It's Ansi.

05:55.088 --> 05:56.489
- What is it that you're doing?

05:56.556 --> 05:58.591
Tell me so I can tell you
why you're doing it wrong.

05:58.658 --> 06:00.293
- Do you know
about these cards?

06:00.359 --> 06:02.195
- Let me show you how it's done.

06:02.261 --> 06:03.296
- Be careful!

06:03.362 --> 06:05.965
- [laughs] Are you kidding?

06:06.032 --> 06:07.166
This will be a breeze.

06:07.233 --> 06:08.101
- [wind gusts]

06:08.167 --> 06:09.502
- Heh!

06:09.569 --> 06:11.704
Uh...uh, that's what's known
as a [unintelligible].

06:11.771 --> 06:13.206
- I will not call him an idiot,

06:13.272 --> 06:15.074
because that's not
what friends do.

06:15.141 --> 06:16.609
Right, Pracky?

06:16.676 --> 06:20.279
- Making friends is easy
when you have things in common,

06:20.346 --> 06:21.981
like real fingers.

06:22.048 --> 06:23.282
- All according to plan!

06:23.349 --> 06:24.817
The drifting activates the--

06:24.884 --> 06:27.153
[groans]

06:27.220 --> 06:29.122
- MASTERSON: Hm.
Well, well, well.

06:29.188 --> 06:30.356
What have we here?

06:30.423 --> 06:31.824
- Our cards!

06:31.891 --> 06:32.859
- I'm on it.

06:32.925 --> 06:33.826
[pants]
- [squeak]

06:33.893 --> 06:35.428
- Sorry, Timbers.

06:35.495 --> 06:37.797
But these are mine now.

06:37.864 --> 06:39.098
- Oh yeah?

06:39.165 --> 06:40.600
I haven't seen
your name on them.

06:43.569 --> 06:44.704
- SARALINE:
What are these cards?

06:44.771 --> 06:46.539
And why does the spy want them?

06:46.606 --> 06:48.007
- [machine whirrs]

06:48.074 --> 06:49.809
- Oh, like I'm gonna tell you?

06:49.876 --> 06:51.677
[pants]

06:51.744 --> 06:52.812
[grunts]

06:52.879 --> 06:53.846
- ALL: The cards!

06:57.483 --> 06:58.851
- Where did the pigeon
come from?

06:58.918 --> 07:01.454
- I guess the spy's not
the only one who wants them.

07:01.521 --> 07:03.723
- Oliver, toss me
your grabbling gun.

07:03.790 --> 07:06.259
- I'd rather eat
a two-pound bag of dog food

07:06.325 --> 07:08.294
or two one-pound bags
of cat food.

07:08.361 --> 07:09.328
- Here, Leif.

07:09.395 --> 07:10.429
- What are you doing?

07:10.496 --> 07:11.697
- I'm sharing.

07:11.764 --> 07:13.399
It's a friend-making thing.

07:15.768 --> 07:16.602
- [coos]

07:16.669 --> 07:19.138
- That's not gonna fly, Pigeon.

07:19.205 --> 07:20.373
- [coos]

07:20.439 --> 07:21.507
- See?

07:21.574 --> 07:23.843
What The Asset wants
he has to get.

07:23.910 --> 07:25.311
[screams]

07:25.378 --> 07:28.481
- [screams]

07:28.548 --> 07:30.783
- Pursuing target.

07:30.850 --> 07:32.084
- [screaming]

07:32.151 --> 07:33.586
- What's the matter?

07:33.653 --> 07:35.288
It's not like we're gonna crash
into the side of the Wayne.

07:35.354 --> 07:36.355
- It is like that!

07:36.422 --> 07:39.258
It's exactly like that!

07:39.325 --> 07:40.426
- OLLY: Oh, you know what?
You're right.

07:40.493 --> 07:41.527
Group scream, anyone?

07:41.594 --> 07:43.863
- [screaming]

07:43.930 --> 07:45.031
- Oh, come on.

07:45.097 --> 07:46.365
Really sell it this time.

07:46.432 --> 07:47.767
- [louder screaming]

07:49.202 --> 07:50.002
- OLLY: I'm just not feeling it.

07:52.471 --> 07:54.006
- [screaming]

07:56.876 --> 07:58.377
- [grunts]

07:58.444 --> 07:59.812
- Aah, help!

07:59.879 --> 08:02.448
Some tiny, vicious creature
is digging his razor claws

08:02.515 --> 08:05.885
into my--oh, hello, Saraline.

08:05.952 --> 08:06.986
- [coos]

08:07.053 --> 08:07.920
- Got 'em.

08:07.987 --> 08:09.856
- [coos]

08:09.922 --> 08:13.426
- [screaming]

08:13.492 --> 08:14.527
[grunting]

08:14.594 --> 08:16.495
- Saraline, do you have
the cards?

08:16.562 --> 08:17.496
- Got 'em.

08:17.563 --> 08:19.632
- Guys, look.

08:19.699 --> 08:21.434
- SARALINE: Whoa.
- ANSI: Whoa.

08:21.500 --> 08:22.869
Where in the Wayne are we?

08:22.935 --> 08:24.770
- LEIF: Ugh, isn't it obvious?

08:24.837 --> 08:26.339
Why, it's so obvious
that I'm going to wait

08:26.405 --> 08:27.907
for one of you to say it.

08:27.974 --> 08:30.276
- This must be
the Wayne postal service.

08:30.343 --> 08:33.212
- This is
the Wayne postal service.

08:33.279 --> 08:34.413
- We're in a post office?

08:34.480 --> 08:38.083
[gasps] I love
municipal infrastructure.

08:38.150 --> 08:40.019
- FEMALE COMPUTER:
Scanning mail item.

08:40.086 --> 08:41.320
- Here, scan away.

08:41.386 --> 08:42.421
- COMPUTER: I will.

08:42.488 --> 08:43.990
Postcards detected.

08:44.056 --> 08:45.091
- Postcards?

08:45.157 --> 08:46.826
- COMPUTER: What is there,
an echo in here?

08:46.893 --> 08:48.394
- Guys, these are postcards.

08:48.461 --> 08:49.762
Postcards!

08:49.829 --> 08:51.330
- What is there,
an echo in here?

08:51.397 --> 08:53.900
- That means
we have to mail them.

08:53.966 --> 08:54.901
But where?

08:54.967 --> 08:57.503
- COMPUTER: Send via outbox 1A.

08:57.570 --> 08:58.905
- We've got to find outbox 1A.

08:58.971 --> 09:00.339
- I think
there's an echo in here.

09:00.406 --> 09:02.241
- Everyone stop being stupid!

09:02.308 --> 09:05.511
- But where's the outbox?

09:05.578 --> 09:08.281
- COMPUTER: Organic
waste material detected.

09:08.347 --> 09:09.582
- Hey, that's not very nice.

09:09.649 --> 09:11.183
- I've been called worse.

09:11.250 --> 09:12.919
- ALL: Whoa!

09:12.985 --> 09:14.353
[grunting]

09:14.420 --> 09:17.056
- COMPUTER: Organic waste to be
eliminated in laser chopper.

09:17.123 --> 09:17.957
- Laser chopper?

09:18.024 --> 09:19.659
This is my kind of post office.

09:19.725 --> 09:20.960
- LEIF: We have
to get out of here.

09:21.027 --> 09:23.262
- Why? What about
the term "laser chopper"

09:23.329 --> 09:24.597
makes you say that?

09:26.866 --> 09:30.336
- CHOPPER: [zapping]

09:30.403 --> 09:31.871
- [sizzling]

09:31.938 --> 09:33.506
- If anyone knows
how to stop this thing,

09:33.572 --> 09:35.241
now would be a good time
to speak up.

09:35.308 --> 09:36.275
- Think, think!

09:36.342 --> 09:37.877
We're in a real jam here.

09:37.944 --> 09:39.612
- Of course. That's it.

09:39.679 --> 09:41.113
I'll jam the lasers.

09:41.180 --> 09:44.617
- [zapping]

09:44.684 --> 09:46.686
- [grunts]

09:50.690 --> 09:51.657
- See what I did there?

09:51.724 --> 09:54.093
I said jam,
and you took the hint.

09:54.160 --> 09:55.461
Credit taken.

09:55.528 --> 09:56.595
- [growls]

09:56.662 --> 09:58.631
- You can always
turn the other cheek...

09:58.698 --> 10:00.399
when your neck works.

10:00.466 --> 10:02.234
- Thanks for the help, Friend.

10:02.301 --> 10:03.369
- Oh, sorry.

10:03.436 --> 10:05.271
[laughs] I was appreciating
my own genius.

10:05.338 --> 10:06.238
Where were we?

10:06.305 --> 10:07.540
- [buzzer]

10:07.606 --> 10:09.642
- [gasps] I don't believe it.

10:09.709 --> 10:13.813
Guys, I found
Jonah Bishop's missing package.

10:13.879 --> 10:14.780
- What are you doing?

10:14.847 --> 10:16.182
- Going with the flow, Sis.

10:16.248 --> 10:17.450
- What's a flowsis?

10:17.516 --> 10:19.118
- But what about the cards?

10:19.185 --> 10:20.453
- Stop overthinking.

10:20.519 --> 10:21.687
The cards'll get mailed.

10:21.754 --> 10:23.122
Jonah will get his package.

10:23.189 --> 10:24.657
Things will work out.

10:24.724 --> 10:26.125
It'll just happen.

10:28.527 --> 10:30.396
[grunts]

10:30.463 --> 10:31.564
Come on, package.

10:31.630 --> 10:32.999
Can I call you package?

10:33.065 --> 10:34.467
[grunts]

10:34.533 --> 10:36.235
Huh?

10:36.302 --> 10:37.536
[grunts]

10:37.603 --> 10:38.904
Yes!

10:38.971 --> 10:40.906
Man, is Jonah gonna be happy
to see you.

10:40.973 --> 10:43.376
- [buzzer]
- [screams]

10:43.442 --> 10:44.643
Paper cuts!

10:44.710 --> 10:47.380
Oh, the mild, mild chafing!

10:47.446 --> 10:50.282
- [beeps]

10:50.349 --> 10:52.585
- MALE COMPUTER: Laser
malfunction detected.

10:52.651 --> 10:55.187
Repair authorization requested.

10:55.254 --> 10:56.689
- Repair authorized.

10:56.756 --> 10:57.656
- Thank you.

10:57.723 --> 10:59.025
- Thanks accepted.

10:59.091 --> 11:01.827
- You need to learn
to say you're welcome.

11:01.894 --> 11:05.264
- I will when you
learn to say I'm sorry.

11:05.331 --> 11:06.599
- All right, then.

11:06.665 --> 11:08.501
I'm sorry...

11:08.567 --> 11:10.403
you're such a robo-jerk.

11:10.469 --> 11:11.670
- Excuse me?

11:11.737 --> 11:13.672
Excuse me?

11:13.739 --> 11:16.208
Excuse me?

11:16.275 --> 11:17.076
We have these postcards,

11:17.143 --> 11:18.878
and we're looking for outbox 1A.

11:18.944 --> 11:20.112
- How do we get there?

11:20.179 --> 11:21.647
- It's a long way.

11:21.714 --> 11:23.049
- What about the shortcut?

11:23.115 --> 11:25.584
- I was getting
to the shortcut.

11:25.651 --> 11:28.788
- Where's the shortcut?
- [screaming]

11:28.854 --> 11:30.723
- He didn't say "cut."

11:30.790 --> 11:32.625
- He was cut short.

11:32.691 --> 11:34.226
Ha-ha. Ha-ha.

11:34.293 --> 11:35.394
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.

11:37.430 --> 11:39.899
- It really wasn't that funny.

11:39.965 --> 11:42.334
- ALL: [screaming]

11:42.401 --> 11:43.402
- Where are we going?

11:43.469 --> 11:44.703
- I don't know.
I'm all turned around.

11:44.770 --> 11:46.105
- I'm not.

11:46.172 --> 11:48.707
Through discipline, I've learned
to control my senses.

11:48.774 --> 11:50.743
I'm perfectly
attuned to my envi--

11:50.810 --> 11:51.644
- [clank]
- [groans]

11:51.710 --> 11:52.812
Concussing!

11:52.878 --> 11:55.614
- Hate to see
that happen to a friend.

11:55.681 --> 11:57.183
- [grunting]

11:57.249 --> 12:00.219
- Nothing like a good plummet
to get the blood flowing...

12:00.286 --> 12:01.387
out of one's noses.

12:01.454 --> 12:03.255
- Ah! Hello.

12:03.322 --> 12:04.490
Olly, come in.

12:04.557 --> 12:06.225
He's not answering.

12:06.292 --> 12:08.894
- ANSI: Well, why did he have
to go after that stupid package?

12:08.961 --> 12:10.362
I hope he's okay.

12:12.264 --> 12:15.101
- [gasps]

12:15.167 --> 12:16.469
Oh, package,

12:16.535 --> 12:18.971
returning you will finally
help me win over Jonah Bishop.

12:19.038 --> 12:20.773
Then I can focus
on my next goal--

12:20.840 --> 12:22.374
becoming state senator.

12:22.441 --> 12:24.944
It'll take a lot of hard work
and deep focus, but--

12:25.010 --> 12:26.378
Ooh! A button.
- [beeps]

12:26.445 --> 12:27.680
- OLLY: Let's see what happens
if I--whoa!

12:27.746 --> 12:30.182
- [package whistles]

12:30.249 --> 12:32.718
- Package, whatever you do,
please don't pop out

12:32.785 --> 12:33.652
and hit me in the--
- [blast]

12:33.719 --> 12:35.488
- Whoa!

12:35.554 --> 12:37.923
[grunts]

12:45.965 --> 12:47.166
- If that was the shortcut,

12:47.233 --> 12:50.236
the outbox must be behind
one of these doors.

12:50.302 --> 12:51.704
Oh, but which one?

12:51.770 --> 12:53.806
- Well, this one, obviously.

12:53.873 --> 12:54.974
- Hello, children.

12:55.040 --> 12:56.775
- Masterson?
How did he get here?

12:56.842 --> 12:57.743
[grunts]

12:57.810 --> 13:00.346
- ♪

13:09.355 --> 13:12.124
- [groans]

13:12.191 --> 13:13.826
- Run!

13:13.893 --> 13:15.861
- A minor...setback.

13:15.928 --> 13:16.862
- Well, that was easy.

13:16.929 --> 13:18.597
Good guys, one.

13:18.664 --> 13:20.799
Bad guys, lost.

13:20.866 --> 13:23.636
What aspect of this mission
can I improve next?

13:23.702 --> 13:25.304
- That does it!

13:25.371 --> 13:26.305
I can't do it.

13:26.372 --> 13:27.740
I can't be friends
with you, Leif.

13:27.806 --> 13:29.341
- What? Why not?

13:29.408 --> 13:30.809
- You've led us
straight to Masterson.

13:30.876 --> 13:32.912
You're a constant pun factory.

13:32.978 --> 13:34.613
And you're a terrible asset.

13:34.680 --> 13:37.316
- Well, I see.

13:37.383 --> 13:38.417
- [sighs]

13:38.484 --> 13:41.887
Look, it's not you. It's me.

13:41.954 --> 13:43.155
I should just stick to Pracky.

13:43.222 --> 13:46.292
- I'm your friend,
as long as batteries exist.

13:46.358 --> 13:47.526
- Pracky?

13:47.593 --> 13:49.562
I always wanted a Pracky.

13:49.628 --> 13:51.130
- Really?

13:51.197 --> 13:53.832
- Hard as it may be to believe,
I too have had a difficult time

13:53.899 --> 13:55.234
making friends.

13:55.301 --> 13:58.137
But my parents wouldn't
let me have a Pracky.

13:58.204 --> 13:59.605
Too desperate, they said.

13:59.672 --> 14:00.906
Too sad.

14:00.973 --> 14:02.775
Too utterly pathetic.

14:02.841 --> 14:04.310
- Okay, I get it, Leif.

14:04.376 --> 14:06.212
- But I always wondered
if things might have

14:06.278 --> 14:09.348
turned out differently
if I only had...

14:09.415 --> 14:10.616
♪ Pracky ♪

14:10.683 --> 14:12.851
♪ Oh, Pracky ♪

14:12.918 --> 14:14.620
- BOTH: ♪ The practice friend ♪

14:14.687 --> 14:17.990
♪ With 21 phrases ♪

14:18.057 --> 14:20.659
- So I'm gonna let you two
weird it up together,

14:20.726 --> 14:21.627
if that's cool.

14:21.694 --> 14:22.528
- [beam star powers on]

14:22.595 --> 14:23.562
- Olly, do you read?

14:23.629 --> 14:24.663
Are okay?

14:24.730 --> 14:25.631
- Flying high.

14:25.698 --> 14:26.665
Yourself?

14:26.732 --> 14:28.033
- Well,
we can't find the outbox,

14:28.100 --> 14:29.401
Masterson is after us,

14:29.468 --> 14:31.437
and Saraline and Leif
are competing for the title

14:31.503 --> 14:32.805
of most awkward human.

14:32.871 --> 14:33.872
Please help.

14:33.939 --> 14:34.873
- On my way!

14:34.940 --> 14:37.710
- [package zooms]

14:37.776 --> 14:39.912
- Come on.
Maybe the outbox is in here.

14:41.247 --> 14:44.250
- [clanking and whirring]

14:45.484 --> 14:46.685
- Or not.

14:46.752 --> 14:47.686
- Oh, great.

14:47.753 --> 14:48.654
Again.

14:48.721 --> 14:50.189
- Afraid so, kid.

14:50.256 --> 14:51.423
Adios!

14:51.490 --> 14:53.325
[grunts]

14:53.392 --> 14:56.362
- We can't let him get
away with our cards!

14:56.428 --> 14:59.898
- Whoa!

14:59.965 --> 15:01.000
- [whirring]

15:01.066 --> 15:04.536
- This is a minor setback.

15:04.603 --> 15:06.171
- Olly, you saved us.

15:08.340 --> 15:09.308
- Yeah.

15:09.375 --> 15:10.743
When it happened,
it was by accident.

15:10.809 --> 15:12.177
But now it was on purpose.

15:12.244 --> 15:13.846
- Come on.
Let's go find the outbox

15:13.912 --> 15:16.448
and mail these cards.

15:16.515 --> 15:18.083
- [package zooms]

15:19.385 --> 15:21.053
- [coos]
- The pigeon is back.

15:21.120 --> 15:23.656
- You could say it's
staging a real coup.

15:23.722 --> 15:24.823
- [groans]

15:24.890 --> 15:25.958
- [coos]

15:26.025 --> 15:27.993
- ALL: [grunting]

15:29.628 --> 15:30.696
- Our cards!

15:32.698 --> 15:33.666
- [coos]

15:33.732 --> 15:35.901
- Why does everyone
want these cards?

15:35.968 --> 15:37.503
- Go! After that pigeon.

15:39.538 --> 15:40.472
- Hm.

15:40.539 --> 15:42.207
May as well push it again.
- [beeps]

15:44.310 --> 15:45.277
- Wow.

15:45.344 --> 15:46.779
This is the package
you were after?

15:46.845 --> 15:48.080
Now I'm impressed.

15:48.147 --> 15:49.348
- What do you say, Ansi?

15:49.415 --> 15:50.883
Up for a little cannon mannin'?

15:50.949 --> 15:53.719
- I'm more comfortable with
cannon personing, but sure.

15:55.888 --> 15:57.790
- Can you get
a clear shot at him?

15:57.856 --> 15:59.625
- Negative.
We've got to get closer.

15:59.692 --> 16:01.226
- Did you just say negative?

16:01.293 --> 16:02.561
- We're flying in a thing.

16:02.628 --> 16:03.595
It felt right.

16:03.662 --> 16:05.698
- No, I'm saying well done.
Negative.

16:05.764 --> 16:07.666
It sounds so official.

16:07.733 --> 16:09.001
- [zap]

16:09.068 --> 16:11.170
- [coos]

16:11.236 --> 16:13.839
- OLLY: Woo-hoo!
You got the cards back.

16:13.906 --> 16:14.840
- [cooing]

16:14.907 --> 16:15.841
- ALL: [gasping] Aah!

16:15.908 --> 16:17.009
- [cooing]

16:17.076 --> 16:18.477
- Oh, no! It's a whole flock!

16:18.544 --> 16:21.513
- Actually, a group of pigeons
is a knob.

16:21.580 --> 16:24.316
- Actually, it's a knob
of widgeons, which are ducks.

16:24.383 --> 16:26.485
A group of pigeons
is a flock or a flight.

16:28.153 --> 16:30.456
What? I watch
public television sometimes.

16:30.522 --> 16:32.825
- [zapping]

16:32.891 --> 16:33.926
- [cooing]

16:33.992 --> 16:37.963
- [zapping]

16:38.030 --> 16:39.431
- [cooing]

16:39.498 --> 16:41.400
- [zapping]

16:47.773 --> 16:49.108
- Ah-- woo!

16:49.174 --> 16:53.879
[whimpers]

16:53.946 --> 16:56.281
[retches]

16:56.348 --> 16:59.585
- [coos frantically]

16:59.651 --> 17:01.687
- [zapping]

17:01.754 --> 17:03.088
- [beeping]

17:03.155 --> 17:04.123
- Uh, guys?

17:04.189 --> 17:05.290
We're way out of gas.

17:05.357 --> 17:06.625
We need a rest area...

17:06.692 --> 17:08.594
and a gas station.

17:08.660 --> 17:09.928
There, the big one.

17:09.994 --> 17:11.163
I think he's like their...

17:11.230 --> 17:12.964
mother...ship.

17:13.031 --> 17:14.098
- Get me close.

17:14.165 --> 17:15.501
- What?

17:15.567 --> 17:17.803
- It's time to prove
that I'm worthy of the name--

17:17.869 --> 17:21.106
- ♪

17:21.173 --> 17:22.307
- --The Asset.

17:24.810 --> 17:25.978
[grunts]

17:26.044 --> 17:27.045
Ooh, look!

17:27.112 --> 17:29.114
There seems to be
a power switch,

17:29.181 --> 17:32.084
which I will now
risk life and limb to--

17:32.151 --> 17:35.854
- Oh, would you just flip it?

17:35.921 --> 17:37.589
- Ha-ha!

17:37.656 --> 17:38.557
Uh-oh.

17:38.624 --> 17:40.726
Aah!

17:40.793 --> 17:41.827
- [beeping]

17:41.894 --> 17:44.196
- [gasps] Brace, brace!

17:44.263 --> 17:45.230
- SARALINE AND ANSI: What?

17:45.297 --> 17:46.665
- I'm saying brace for a--

17:46.732 --> 17:49.568
- [clanking]

17:49.635 --> 17:50.836
- OLLY: I was gonna say
long winter.

17:52.004 --> 17:53.772
- Oh! Got 'em!

17:55.207 --> 17:56.842
- [groaning]

17:56.909 --> 17:58.177
- Thanks, Leif.

17:58.243 --> 18:00.712
- Have I proven myself
as an asset?

18:00.779 --> 18:01.947
- Ish.

18:02.014 --> 18:04.283
Uh, look!

18:04.349 --> 18:07.286
- ANSI: Guys,
this must be outbox 1A.

18:07.352 --> 18:10.956
Now we can mail these cards.

18:11.023 --> 18:12.224
- [beeps]

18:12.291 --> 18:13.058
- MALE COMPUTER:
Delivery rejected.

18:13.125 --> 18:14.259
- [buzzer]

18:14.326 --> 18:15.294
- COMPUTER: Mail routed
through outbox

18:15.360 --> 18:17.996
must arrive
by PG1 delivery system.

18:18.063 --> 18:20.065
- What's a PG1 delivery system?

18:20.132 --> 18:22.201
- [whirring]

18:22.267 --> 18:23.735
- [grunting]

18:25.671 --> 18:28.974
- Looks like I'm holding
all the cards now.

18:29.041 --> 18:31.376
[grunts]

18:31.443 --> 18:33.145
- You.
- That's right.

18:33.212 --> 18:34.213
Me.

18:34.279 --> 18:35.881
- That's...what I said.

18:35.948 --> 18:37.282
- So did I.
- Well, good.

18:37.349 --> 18:38.951
- Fine.
- Get him!

18:42.855 --> 18:46.291
- ALL: [screaming]

18:47.893 --> 18:48.927
- He's getting away!

18:48.994 --> 18:49.962
- [grunts]

18:50.028 --> 18:53.665
- Very, very slowly.

18:53.732 --> 18:56.401
- [gasps]

18:56.468 --> 18:57.836
Huh.

18:57.903 --> 18:59.938
Wait, I got it.

19:00.005 --> 19:01.673
The pigeons aren't our enemies.

19:01.740 --> 19:02.875
They work here.

19:02.941 --> 19:05.110
They were trying to help us
mail the cards.

19:05.177 --> 19:06.245
- Oh.

19:06.311 --> 19:08.046
Of course they were
being helpful.

19:08.113 --> 19:10.115
They work at the post office.

19:10.182 --> 19:11.717
- Look at the symbol
on the bottom.

19:11.783 --> 19:14.720
They must be
the PG1 delivery system.

19:14.786 --> 19:16.154
- He's right.

19:16.221 --> 19:18.190
- [grunts]

19:18.257 --> 19:19.558
- ANSI: Hey, Masterson!

19:19.625 --> 19:20.392
- [groans]

19:20.459 --> 19:21.994
- I'm scheduling a pickup.

19:22.060 --> 19:23.262
And there's no...

19:23.328 --> 19:24.730
signature...

19:24.796 --> 19:26.431
required.

19:26.498 --> 19:29.067
- So you're just gonna
leave it by the door,

19:29.134 --> 19:30.769
where someone can steal it?

19:30.836 --> 19:33.505
- Actually, that was
my tough guy line.

19:33.572 --> 19:34.406
- Oh.

19:34.473 --> 19:35.974
I totally didn't get that.

19:38.644 --> 19:41.680
- [beeps]

19:41.747 --> 19:44.883
[coos]

19:47.653 --> 19:50.956
- [grunts]

19:51.023 --> 19:53.926
- Mail those cards, boys!

19:53.992 --> 19:55.427
- Wait a minute.

19:55.494 --> 19:57.696
So if we just let the pigeon
take the cards on the roof,

19:57.763 --> 19:59.498
we wouldn't have had
to do any of this.

19:59.565 --> 20:03.969
- [coos]

20:04.036 --> 20:06.905
- [beeps]

20:06.972 --> 20:08.874
- [coos]

20:08.941 --> 20:10.509
- [machine whirrs]

20:13.345 --> 20:14.479
- [coos]

20:14.546 --> 20:16.381
- COMPUTER: Delivery accepted.

20:16.448 --> 20:18.850
Three postcards
received for processing.

20:18.917 --> 20:20.619
- We sent something...

20:20.686 --> 20:21.820
somewhere!

20:21.887 --> 20:23.255
- We did it!
- Yes!

20:23.322 --> 20:25.624
- Woo!
- Yes! Ha-ha! Yeah.

20:25.691 --> 20:28.126
- [grunts]

20:28.193 --> 20:30.629
I couldn't
get the cards.

20:30.696 --> 20:32.164
- [sighs]

20:32.230 --> 20:34.299
Did you at least get the milk?

20:34.366 --> 20:35.667
- [groans]

20:35.734 --> 20:36.602
- [thud]

20:38.136 --> 20:39.338
- You're an asset, Leif.

20:39.404 --> 20:41.273
But you're our asset.

20:41.340 --> 20:42.608
Thanks for your help.

20:42.674 --> 20:44.676
- Couldn't do it without...

20:44.743 --> 20:45.544
friends?

20:45.611 --> 20:47.512
- [car horn honks]
- Here.

20:47.579 --> 20:50.882
I think Pracky needs someone
who appreciates him like I do.

20:50.949 --> 20:51.984
- Really?

20:52.050 --> 20:54.152
- Sometimes friends
outgrow each other,

20:54.219 --> 20:55.954
if one of them is real.

20:56.021 --> 20:59.324
- Oh, Saraline, this is
the happiest moment of my...

20:59.391 --> 21:01.126
afternoon.

21:01.193 --> 21:04.296
- You know, I think
I've learned something today.

21:04.363 --> 21:06.164
You can't force friendship.

21:06.231 --> 21:07.799
Sometimes you have to go
to a post office

21:07.866 --> 21:11.670
and fight robots and--yeah,
I learned nothing today.

21:11.737 --> 21:14.673
- We learned nothing together.

21:16.174 --> 21:18.377
- ♪

21:22.848 --> 21:23.982
- Olly...

21:24.049 --> 21:25.350
Well done.

21:27.419 --> 21:28.453
What the--

21:28.520 --> 21:30.789
Man, this thing
is totally broken!

21:30.856 --> 21:32.090
- Run.

21:32.157 --> 21:33.191
- [car horn honks]

21:33.258 --> 21:35.127
- Okay, so what just happened?

21:35.193 --> 21:36.461
And what were those cards?

21:36.528 --> 21:38.563
And where did we
just mail them to?

21:38.630 --> 21:39.898
- I don't know, buddy.

21:39.965 --> 21:42.034
But we went with the flow,
and it worked out.

21:42.100 --> 21:43.101
- Go with the flow?

21:43.168 --> 21:44.803
I saw that on a t-shirt once.

21:44.870 --> 21:46.872
- All I know
is there must be a reason

21:46.938 --> 21:47.973
why I came to the Wayne.

21:48.040 --> 21:49.341
- Well, obviously.

21:49.408 --> 21:51.043
To be the yin to my yang.

21:51.109 --> 21:52.611
Or the yang to my yin.

21:52.678 --> 21:54.246
Oh, what are you?
More of a yang guy?

21:54.312 --> 21:55.747
- Let's just go watch
"Bobby and Tommy."

21:58.850 --> 21:59.718
- [zap]

22:02.087 --> 22:05.724
- ♪
